===Etymology===
From the Latin ''Canariae insulae'', "[[Canary Islands]]" (Spanish "Islas Canarias"); from the largest island ''Insula Canaria'' ("Dog Island" or "Canine Island"), named for its dogs, from ''[[canarius]]'', "canine", from ''[[canis]]'', dog.

